                            <comment id="14143132" author="ashish singhi" created="Mon, 22 Sep 2014 12:01:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The following will be help message after applying the patch.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
Here is some help &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt; command:
Alter a table. If &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;hbase.online.schema.update.enable&quot;&lt;/span&gt; property is set to &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;false&lt;/span&gt;,
then table must be disabled &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; need not be disabled (see help &apos;disable&apos;).
You can add/modify/delete column families, as well as change table
configuration. Column families work similarly to create; column family
spec can either be a name string, or a dictionary with NAME attribute.
Dictionaries are described on the main help command output.
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please review&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14143366" author="stack" created="Mon, 22 Sep 2014 16:25:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=misty&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;misty&quot;&gt;Misty Stanley-Jones&lt;/a&gt; Want to review this when you get back from the beach?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14154236" author="misty" created="Wed, 1 Oct 2014 02:15:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is a good improvement. Here is some feedback:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please don&apos;t skip articles (a, an, the):&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;s/If &quot;hbase.online...&quot;/If the &quot;hbase.online...&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
s/then table/then the table&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, &quot;then table must be disabled else need not be disabled&quot; reads like a shell script. How about something like &quot;then the table must be disabled. If h.o.s.u.enable is set to true, tables can be altered without disabling them first.&quot; Also, do you need to mention any potential risk to enabling it?  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Maybe &quot;You can use the alter command to add, modify, or delete column families or change table configuration options.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;s/similarly to create/in a similar way as the create command&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;s/column family spec/the column family specification&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;s/dictionary with NAME attribute/dictionary with the NAME attribute&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;s/described on the main help command output/described in the output of the &apos;help&apos; command, with no arguments.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t see a need to be extremely compact in help text. Does that make sense?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14154403" author="misty" created="Wed, 1 Oct 2014 05:56:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The new patch looks great. The only thing missing (if necessary) is a mention of the possible dangers of altering a table that is not disabled. Is it dangerous? I would assume so, since the default is not to allow it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14154405" author="ashish singhi" created="Wed, 1 Oct 2014 05:57:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Misty for such a nice feedback.&lt;br/&gt;
Please check whether second patch addresses your points.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Also, do you need to mention any potential risk to enabling it? &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I do not think so. If it was risky then we would not have enabled it by default. See &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-7639&quot; title=&quot;Enable online schema update by default &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-7639&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-7639&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14154411" author="stack" created="Wed, 1 Oct 2014 06:02:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;A word of caution would not go amiss.  This feature has been buggy in the past and its my guess that it sees little use &amp;#8211; just saying.  Want to commit and add a note on commit &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=misty&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;misty&quot;&gt;Misty Stanley-Jones&lt;/a&gt;? Else I can.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
